    • Rs 100 crore scholarship scam: ED searches at 7 places in 4 districts of UP

    Rs 100 crore scholarship scam: ED searches at 7 places in 4 districts of UP

    TNN / Updated: Feb 17, 2023, 05:12 IST

    TimesPoints

    8580
    Share
    AA
    Text Size
    • Small
    • Medium
    • Large

    ARTICLES

    Image used for representational purpose only
    LUCKNOW : The Enforcement Directorate (ED) on Thursday carried out searches at seven locations in four districts of Uttar Pradesh, including Lucknow, Sitapur, Hardoi and Farrukhabad, in connection with a scam worth around Rs 100 crore involving scholarship for disabled students, which allegedly continued from 2013 to 2017 in the state. The ED had registered a case under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act in December 2022 in connection with the scam. The ED searches are on the premises of medical educational institutes offering courses in pharma studies. The institutes are accused of receiving scholarships in the name of students who were never enrolled, and fake certificates were produced to get scholarship grants from the state government.
    The ED said that investigations revealed that private medical institutes had connived with government officials, whose roles are being scanned, to procure release of scholarship funds for students who never existed. The team first searched the premises of a private medical institute in Madiaon area of Lucknow, while searches were carried out simultaneously in Sitapur, Hardoi and Farrukhabad. The UP vigilance department took up the investigation of the case after registering an FIR in 2017. Later, seeing the magnitude of the case, it was taken up by the ED for further probe.
    Sources in the ED said that they have sought documents pertaining to students enrolled between 2013 and 2017 and the fees paid by those students during their course of study from medical institutions. "Authorities of these medical colleges were asked to present these documents before the ED zonal office within ten days," sources privy to the probe added. The sources said that the scam could even be much more than Rs 100 crore. The ED has currently taken up those institutes, the names of which had cropped up during the probe by the vigilance establishment of UP.
